# Snyk (https://snyk.io) policy file — KataHarness
# Operator: taurran@gmail.com
# Created: 2026-06-30
#
# SUPPRESSION RATIONALE — python/PT (CWE-23 Path Traversal) in tools/kata_install.py
#
# Every python/PT LOW finding in this file is a false positive. _safe_abs() is the
# CWE-23 boundary guard: it rejects any path whose components include '..' via
#   any(part == ".." for part in p.parts)
# before resolving, and is called at every external-input entry point. Snyk's taint
# engine does not recognise this Python idiom as a sanitizer, so it marks downstream
# path operations (shutil.rmtree, shutil.copytree, Path / concatenation) as tainted.
# (Snyk's reported count varies with taint-propagation changes; the file-level ignore
# below is count-independent and blankets every python/PT finding in this file.)
#
# Additional constraint: several of these findings land inside the 5 byte-frozen engine
# fns (_link_or_copy, _flat_link_skills, install, copy_project, confirm_platform) that
# cannot receive inline # snyk:ignore comments without breaking the byte-freeze.
#
# Risk class: operator-controlled local CLI tool; all paths are operator-supplied and
# validated at the _safe_abs boundary. Residual risk is negligible.
# Severity: LOW (every python/PT finding here). No medium+ findings present.
#
# Risk accepted under Approach C (documented suppression). Review by: 2027-06-30.
# SUPPRESSION RATIONALE — python/CommandInjection (CWE-78) in adapters/claude/statusline_chain.py
#
# One MEDIUM finding: argv -> subprocess.run. FALSE POSITIVE, gate-adjudicated (context-autonomy
# A2 task gate + delta gate, 2026-07-04): the argv derives EXCLUSIVELY from the operator's own
# ~/.claude/settings.json statusLine.command — a value the Claude Code host already executes via
# shell. The wrapper executes the same command with strictly LESS privilege: shell=False list-argv,
# shlex-plain-parse-or-SKIP eligibility, full shell-metacharacter gate (incl. cmd-only % ^), and
# .bat/.cmd/.com targets SKIP-ineligible (implicit-cmd.exe vector closed; extensionless PATHEXT
# residual disproven live — CreateProcess appends only .exe). Exhaustive taint check: stdin, env,
# and bridge content never influence argv. See adapters/claude/README.md §security and the
# protocol/exec-safety.md registry row (C10).
#
# Risk accepted (documented suppression). Review by: 2027-01-04 (6-month review — execution sink).

version: v1.25.0
ignore:
  python/CommandInjection:
    - 'adapters/claude/statusline_chain.py':
        reason: >-
          FALSE POSITIVE, gate-adjudicated: argv derives exclusively from the operator's own
          settings.json statusLine.command, which the host already shell-executes; the wrapper
          runs it with strictly less privilege (shell=False list-argv, shlex-or-SKIP, full
          metachar gate incl. % ^, batch targets SKIP-ineligible, PATHEXT residual disproven).
          No less-trusted taint path (stdin/env/bridge never reach argv). MEDIUM, single finding.
          Registry row in protocol/exec-safety.md (C10). Expiry: 2027-01-04.
        expires: '2027-01-04T00:00:00.000Z'
  python/PT:
    - 'tools/kata_install.py':
        reason: >-
          FALSE POSITIVE: _safe_abs() rejects '..' traversal at every external-input
          boundary via `any(part == ".." for part in p.parts)` — Snyk's taint engine
          does not recognise this idiom as a sanitizer. Several findings are in the 5
          byte-frozen engine fns that cannot accept inline snyk:ignore comments.
          Operator-controlled local CLI; all paths are operator-supplied. Severity: LOW.
          File-level ignore is count-independent. Risk accepted per Approach C. Expiry: 2027-06-30.
        expires: '2027-06-30T00:00:00.000Z'
    - 'tools/kata_host_settings.py':
        reason: >-
          FALSE POSITIVE: same _safe_abs '..'-rejection class as tools/kata_install.py
          (D152 host-settings merge module, 2026-07-12) — Snyk's taint engine does not
          credit the guard idiom. Operator-controlled local CLI editing the operator's
          own ~/.claude/settings.json behind an explicit consent flag. Severity: LOW.
          Risk accepted per Approach C, same rationale/expiry as the sibling entry.
        expires: '2027-06-30T00:00:00.000Z'
patch: {}
